        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid possible property damage and/or personal injury, park the vehicle on a level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>It is difficult to remove the lift spring from the lift spring bracket while the bracket is
                        installed to the hood. When removing the lift spring bracket the lift spring should remain
                        attached to the bracket. After the bracket is removed the lift spring can be removed from the
                        bracket. To install the lift spring bracket, attach the lift spring to the bracket then install
                        the bracket and spring to the hood.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0390101" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g039016.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Remove Lift Spring Bracket With Spring Attached</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0390102" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g039015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Remove Lift Spring from Bracket</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">9900i Model only:</emph>
                    Remove the hood bumper stop bracket and hood lift spring brackets, with the lift spring attached
                    (Figure 1), from the hood. Remove the lift spring bracket from the lift spring (Figure 2). Identify
                    the hood bumper stop brackets for driver and passenger side reassembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">9900ix Model only:</emph>
                    Remove the driver and passenger side hood lift spring brackets, with the lift spring attached, from
                    the hood.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">9900i Model only:</emph>
                    Reinstall the hood bumper stop bracket with the new design hood lift spring brackets, with the lift
                    spring attached (Figure 3 and Figure 4), to the driver and passenger side. Tighten the bolts to 15
                    Lbf-ft (20 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">9900ix Model only :</emph>
                    Install new design hood lift spring brackets, with the lift spring attached, to the driver and
                    passenger side (Figure 3). Note, in addition to the original bracket bolts use two (2) Part Number
                    411431C2 bolts. Tighten to 15 Lbf-ft (20 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">9900i Model only:</emph>
                    Close the hood and check hood alignment. Adjust the hood stop bumper brackets as needed.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f039013" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g039013.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Install New Lift Spring Bracket (9900i and 9900ix Models)</caption>
